- rust_proxy is a developer tool used by both humans and AI coding agents
- Premium visual output increases perceived quality and professionalism
- Better output formatting reduces cognitive load when reading status/diagnostics
- Consistent styling across all commands creates a cohesive product feel

## Critical Constraint: Agent Safety
The PRIMARY users of rust_proxy are AI coding agents (Claude Code, Codex, Gemini). These agents parse CLI output to make decisions. Therefore:
- ALL --json output MUST remain unchanged and machine-parseable
- Piped output (non-TTY) MUST be plain text without ANSI codes
- Environment variables like NO_COLOR, CI, CLAUDE_CODE must be respected
- Rich formatting is ONLY for human-interactive terminal sessions

